-- 
2011-09-15T06:07:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/enbw-seeks-1-1-billion-from-shareholders-handelsblatt-reports.html
EnBW Energie Baden-Wuerttemberg AG (EBK) 
will ask its two largest shareholders for 800 million euros
($1.1 billion) to help fund its switch to renewable energy from
nuclear power, Handelsblatt reported, citing unidentified people
close to the company.  Hans Peter Villis, the Karlsruhe, Germany-based utilityâ€™s
chief executive officer, will present the plan to Baden
Wuerrtemberg and the OEW association of municipalities in the
southern German state at a Sept. 22 supervisory board meeting,
the newspaper said.  OEW and Baden Wuerttemberg together hold more than 93
percent of EnBW, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
